script is named:

~/.local/bin/xdg-open

And contains the following:

#!/bin/bash

echo "go to xdg-open"
XDG_CURRENT_DESKTOP=X-Generic /usr/bin/xdg-open $@

The script will simply set the XDG_CURRENT_DESKTOP and then run xdg-open normally
---

Taken from https://www.reddit.com/r/kde/comments/zm6gag/prevent_a_browser_window_from_changing_virtual/
